<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1898,1997]" pageId="5" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1899,1925]" pageId="5" pageNumber="265">Remarks.</emphasis>
The validity of this genus was discussed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Pinto, J. D." box="[779,1054,1899,1925]" pageId="5" pageNumber="265" pagination="2013 - 2102" refId="ref24219" refString="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Pinto, J. D. (2002) The Old World genera of Meloidae (Coleoptera): a key and synopsis. Journal of Natural History, 36, 2013 - 2102. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930110062318" type="journal article" year="2002">Bologna &amp; Pinto (2002)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Batelka, J. &amp; Hajek, J." box="[1111,1388,1898,1925]" pageId="5" pageNumber="265" pagination="123 - 130" refId="ref24117" refString="Batelka, J. &amp; Hajek, J. (2015) New synonyms, combinations and faunistic records in the genus Denierella Kaszab (Coleoptera: Meloidae). Zootaxa, 4000 (1), 123 - 130. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4000.1.6" type="journal article" year="2015">Batelka &amp; HÃ¡jek (2015)</bibRefCitation>
. We also considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaszab" authorityYear="1952" box="[330,449,1935,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Denierella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[330,449,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="265">Denierella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably a subgenus of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1834" box="[854,955,1935,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Epicauta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[854,955,1935,1960]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="265">Epicauta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, this problem should be resolved by a phylogenetic analysis to the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parker &amp; Boving" authorityYear="1925" box="[583,701,1971,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Epicautini">Epicautini</taxonomicName>
, including all genera and subgenera.
</paragraph>
